  "title": "BARBER",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p><p>The Senior Barber is responsible for providing professional barbering services and ensuring high standards of grooming, hygiene, and customer satisfaction. The role includes supervising junior barbers, maintaining service quality, and supporting daily salon operations.</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>Perform professional haircuts, beard trimming, shaving, and grooming services</p><p>Consult with customers to understand their style and grooming preferences</p><p>Supervise and guide junior barbers and assistants</p><p>Maintain cleanliness, hygiene, and sterilization of tools and workstations</p><p>Ensure compliance with health, safety, and workplace regulations</p><p>Manage daily workstation setup and closing procedures</p><p>Assist in inventory control of barber tools, products, and supplies</p><p>Handle customer feedback and resolve service-related issues professionally</p><p>Support salon promotions and customer retention activities</p><p>Requirements & Skills<br /></p><p>Strong understanding of salon hygiene and sterilization procedures</p><p>Safe handling of razors, blades, and sharp tools</p><p>Compliance with workplace safety and health standards</p><p>Cleanliness and sanitation of workstations and common areas</p><p>Proven experience as a Barber or Senior Barber</p><p>Strong knowledge of modern and traditional barbering techniques</p><p>Ability to train and supervise junior staff</p><p>Good customer service and communication skills</p><p>Knowledge of hygiene, sanitation, and safety standards</p><p>Ability to work independently and as part of a team</p><p>Qualifications</p><p>Certificate or diploma in barbering / hairdressing (preferred)</p><p>Minimum 3–5 years of relevant work experience</p>",
